description: After the Marsupilami causes a series of disasters, Spirou and Fantasio finally resolve to bring the strange animal back to its birth place, Palombia. Unfortunately, it’s a nation in turmoil they find upon their arrival. The military is all-powerful, rumours of impending war are growing and a ruthless tyrant has seized power. To counter the dictator’s plans, the two adventurers’ only weapon is the Count of Champignac’s latest outrageous invention: a mushroom extract that makes metals go soft…
name: The Dictator and the Mushroom

description:
76 pages of claw-popping action!

Wolverine faces a hopeless battle as Sabretooth, Mystique and the Hand strike! Has the end finally come? Don't miss 'Killable" by Paul Cornell and Alan Davis!

Deadpool heads back to the 1960s for a Kirbyesque kosmic klassic! By Gerry Duggan, Brian Posehn and Scott Koblish!

Bonus story: Deadpool tracks the dreaded Chupacabra, the goat-sucker, in Mexico! 'Mouth of the Border' is by Cullen Bunn and Matteo Scalera!

Featuring material first printed in Wolverine #12-13, Deadpool #20 and Deadpool #1000.

Second Son

After crash landing on Malsum Island, the Vatican Black Ops attempt to infiltrate ReGen Corp's remote cloning facility in hopes of stealing the recreated Christ.
name: Episode 3: Second Son

description: The Doctor and company travel to the city of Casablanca to discover all is not as it seems. The city streets are filled with Nazis, Silurians and a familiar looking bar owner.
name: As Time Goes By: Part 1

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: Special issue by Eisner-nominated writer Joshua Hale Fialkov! With Rory in the custody of the local police, the Doctor searches the deserted and fog-filled city of Casablanca. What he stumbles upon may spell the end for not just two recently reunited lovers, but for all of mankind!
name: As Time Goes By: Part 2

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: Special arc by Eisner-nominated writer Joshua Hale Fialkov! At the onset of World War II, the Silurian's scheme of world domination has come to light - and they want Amy as their queen! Can the Doctor stop the reptilian aliens and their unwitting Nazi allies? Of course he can. He's the Doctor!
name: As Time Goes By: Part 3

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: This special arc by Eisner-nominated writer Joshua Hale Fialkov concludes! The Silurian plan is revealed, apocalypse imminent, and with mere minutes to go, can the Doctor and his strange new ally save not just Casablanca but the entire human race?
name: As Time Goes By: Part 4

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: The battle for the future of humanity rages on, as Imperiex faces three angry superhumans! But it’s hard to present a united front when everyone thinks they should be in charge.
name: Genesis - Part 8 of 9

description: Will our headstrong heroes learn to work together—or will the Justice League’s first mission be its last?
name: Genesis - Part 9 of 9

description:
'It is said that whosoever desecrates the ancient temple of the Corazan shall meet their maker within the passing of two moons.'

1941, Burma - Archaeologist Charles Simmons, and his assistant, Alan, may finally have located the lost temple that has been Simmons' lifelong goal, and nothing, not even tales of a deadly curse, will get in their way.

But when Delia, the beautiful young wife of the powerful businessman beneath whose land the temple is buried, falls in love with Alan, that curse may be the least of their troubles.

Accidents that may not be as innocent as they seem are just the beginning! Then comes the news that the Japanese army is on the march... and Burma, and the lost city, lies directly in their path!
name: Forbidden Love

description:
'I always wanted to be a nurse, but since school I've taken any work that was going. Now I've got a real job - a career even!'

When she set out to find a job that would let her help people, the last place Jo Gibbs expected to find herself was on a trip round Spain, and the last people she expected to share the journey with was a group of old ladies, unofficially led by the imperious Lady Vernon.

Not much chance for romance on a pensioners' road trip? Not unless you count Ted, the driver with glint in his eye, or Lady Vernon's wealthy grandson...

But this unexpected trip in unexpected company has a few even more unexpected turns to take before it's over, and Jo's desire to help others might just leave her feeling utterly helpless herself!
name: Journey To Love

description:
'Yes, Jarmyle, you will be mine... and I shall bring you back to life again.'

1815, Somerset - The beautiful Miss Caroline Bennet, newly arrived in England from Boston, has eyes only for the proud Jarmyle Hall, once her family home, until it was lost to the despicable Lord Grantley - the man who shot her father dead in a duel.

But with Grantley now dead, Jarmyle lies in the hands of his nephew, John... And John has fallen in love with Caroline!

'Love? A fragile bauble... it can be lost at a whim, by fate... a murderer's bullet, for example.'

Thus begins a tale of coldly-served revenge. But will new passions begin to warm Caroline's heart?
name: Mistress Of Jarmyle

description:
'You'll be all right, Miss Price. But you're going to need someone strong... someone to lean on.'

Yolande Price had it all - high-flying career as a television executive, a handsome producer boyfriend, the chance to work hard and play harder. Then, on what should have been a glorious Mediterranean holiday, a mysterious illness brought the party crashing to a halt.

Back in the UK, and recuperating in a private mansion house clinic, in the care of brusque and demanding Dr Alan Grant, Yolande finds her relationship strained to breaking point. New love is waiting in the wings... but so is tragedy!

To get through all of this, Yolande will need to find special strength. And if not her own, someone to be strong for her!
name: The Loving Touch

description:
'What I need is a new image... a new Gail for a new job.'

As personal assistant, Gail Coe was tired of bosses trying to get too up close and personal with her. So, looking to change her luck, she opted for a change of image.

To ensure it was her skills that got noticed, not her looks, she set about transforming herself. Goodbye to Gail. Hello to prim, businesslike Miss Coe.

So when Oliver Sanders not only hired her but took her out to the jungles of the Bahamas to survey potential oil field sites, she knew it was all down to her qualifications... Wasn't it?
name: No Time For Love

description:
'You're young and strong. Adam wasn't interested in you until he realised you were ideal mother material.'

Magda Bannerman's words were like a cold slap to Laura Marshall. Laura had come to the private island to care for Magda's children. But, between her nannying duties and fending off her employer's lecherous husband, she had come to care even more deeply for Adam Bannerman, Magda's brother-in-law.

'Rich, powerful men don't marry servants.'

But with what Magda reveals of Adam's secret past, will the servant still be prepared to marry the rich, powerful man?
name: Follow Your Heart

description:
Swallowing the Omphalos

With Malus' plot seemingly revealed, Prometheus takes far-reaching actions across the Corporate Space. At the same time, an opportunity presents itself against Prometheus that the Torchbearers cannot ignore.
name: Swallowing the Omphalos

description:
Above Hyperian Skies

A new mission forces the Torchbearers to have a direct confrontation against Prometheus Inc's Main Collector.
name: Above Hyperian Skies

description: A young warrior prince learns what it takes to become a great leader.
name: Prince Ahmad

description: Exhausted and baffled, Agent Paulson returns home. But danger is in pursuit and this time, Paulson has put his family at risk. Can he protect them?
After pulling the ol' switcheroo, Batman gets the jump on the Suicide Squad! But does he have enough tricks up his sleeve to take them all on at once?
name: Who Wants To Kill A Billionaire? Part 3 of 4

story_arc_credits.name: Who Wants To Kill A Billionaire?

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Who Wants To Kill A Billionaire?

description: When Olivia tracks down Charlie, their conversation turns into a fight that cannot easily be won.

volume.name: The Battle of the Blood Moon

description:
Bold Blood (conclusion) & Ogre's Lot

The foray into the Unholy Wood comes to a fatal conclusion. Who among the working-class warriors survived? Also in this issue: Ogre seeks to improve his lowly stature among his fellow men by stealing Hermann's fabled magic sword Aelfhere. Created by Joe St.Pierre (Marvel, DC, Image, Valiant, IDW, New Zodiax)
name: Bold Blood (Conclusion) & Ogre's Lot

description:
CY-BOAR #5: THE INTRUDER

A mutated cybernetic boar searches for his place in the world. Looking for peace, Cy-boar usually finds only danger, and skull splitting action!

Cy-Boar stumbles upon another secret outpost deep in the woods. What's he do? ATTACK!!!

SCORP #1: SILENT INTERLUDE

Little is known about the man called Scorp. He was recruited for the Pentagon team from the CIA, highly skilled in exotic martial arts of an unknown style, he carries a spring loaded stick weapons that can unfold into a number of different configurations. Where is he really from? He is still searching for these answers...

Scorp attempts a daring rescue to free a scientist from heavily armed members of the Crimson Militia in this silent tale.
name: The Intruder; Silent Interlude

description:
Grounded

Val disappears from the hospital and no one knows how it happened. If seeing is believing then these people have seen something they would never forget. Then we follow the old man into a homeless shelter, and got refused help... what would you do?
name: Grounded

description:
"CONVERSATIONS WITH THE DEAD"

After the ghosts of Corinne's fallen teammates impart a mysterious gift to her, she's attacked by a new breed of cybernetic zombie that will change her forever.
name: Conversations With the Dead

description:
Expectant Mother

Lightning Lady's mother drops in for a surprise visit and starts pressuring her daughter about her lack of a boyfriend. When Lightning Lady lies about her romantic situation, it leads her down a path that leads her back into her own past.

And in the special bonus feature, what happens when Lightning Lady plans a heist? She has to ward off more than pesky heroes when she realizes that one of the henchmen has eyes for her.
name: Expectant Mother

description: This issue features "Mister Chameleon". The master of disguise must find a canister of deadly nerve gas. And a new "Clinic for Alien Research" stories. How weird can things get when a homeowner finds an alien in his freezer.

Lord of the Abyss

Something is stirring on the docks of Darkport. The Haunter aims to find out what that stirring is. He may just be in over his head.
name: Lord of the Abyss

description:
Beckett and Duran utilize Duran’s gift of discernment to track down the person (or persons) responsible for Arlington’s missing children. Another victim puts the city on lockdown, with curfew in full effect as Arlington’s police patrol the town streets twenty-four hours a day.

Meanwhile, a new player has entered the field, looking for her prize: the true innocent.

John L. Sullivan learns what Mr. X means when he says he can be champion on OTHER worlds. He reveals his true form, introduces John to his grizzled veteran trainer Buque, and forms a partnership that is mostly prisoner. John L. Sullivan accepts the new challenges with his usual bravado.

volume.name: John L. Sullivan Boston Strong Boy In Space

description: You've heard the story. Now learn the truth. In this book-length epic, from out of the Golden Age of Heroes, the secret origin of THE GOLDEN WARRIOR will at last be revealed. This is not the romanticized version Flare once told to Icicle. Beginning in this issue of LIBERTY COMICS, with story by Dennis Mallonee and artwork by Keith Dotson, learn the unvarnished truth behind the saga of Katrina Feran, Katrina of the valkyrior, the woman who would one day give birth to the world's greatest heroine.

The Mighty Thor adds another volume to his saga of Asgardian adventure as the Marvel Masterworks roll on! Thor is lucky to have the mighty Hercules at his side - because Loki has teamed with Firelord in a bid to usurp Odin's throne! Meanwhile, Jane Foster has returned, and Thor is torn between aiding her on Earth and remaining in defense of Asgard! And when the Absorbing Man and Ulik the Troll enter the fray, the drama reaches epic proportions that will have you on the edge of your seat! Before it's over, Thor will battle the gods of Egypt to save Odin from death itself. And to top off this voluminous volume, we're including a rare Hercules solo tale from Marvel Premiere! Collecting THOR (1966) #229-241 and MARVEL PREMIERE #26.

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular Edition CoverGil Kane1
DMDirect Market Edition CoverGil Kane2
name: Volume 14

description:
Last we met our intrepid heroes they were selling comic books, playing video games and DISSAPEARING FROM ALL OF REALITY?! WHAT'S HAPPENING TO MASS? WHY IS THIS HAPPENING? WHAT MADNESS IS THIS? WHAT DASTARDLY VILLAIN COULD CONCEIVE SUCH A PLOT? And who is that coffee addicted old man in that spectacular hat.

Find out all this and more in Massively Effective #2 Electric Boogaloo! No, wait, that's not right. Massively Effective #2! In a story aptly titled "The more things change, the more they stay the same" Part 2.

Serious New Stuff

Happy April fools day! What's inside this issue? Not much and what there is, doesn't make much sense. But it's there anyway.
name: Serious New Stuff

description:
Cricket

For millennia, the celestial energies of the Zodiac have been available to those whose consciousness is open to their manipulation. Introducing the New Pisces, the paranormal investigator named CRICKET! Plus the hacker THE LIBERAIDER comes head to head with the urban scavenger gang called THE DREGS.

Created by Joe St.Pierre (Marvel, DC, Image, Valiant, IDW).
name: Cricket

description:
A Fright At the Opera!

Our saga resumes with our hero battling an epic existential crisis: Ward Woodcock's lost his fortune, his reputation, his sidekick -- and even his "so called" super friends have turned against him. Could there possibly be a worse time for Nightwasp to have a final showdown with the Hen at the Metro City Opera House? If you like opera and superheroes, this issue is a MUST READ!!

Also, this issue features brilliant artwork within by Short Fuse Media and cover art by Nightwasp's very own creator!
name: A Fright At the Opera!

volume.name: Nightwasp: The Man Who Is Hardly Ever Afraid

description: Oh Joy, Sex Toy: Volume Two is a hefty 328 pages of comics by Erika Moen. This volume collects the second year's worth of content from the weekly comic Oh Joy Sex Toy, covering all kinds of sex, in the form of toy reviews, education pieces, interviews and more. With her positivity, terrible puns and diverse cast, Volume Two is an indispensable resource for anybody exploring comics or their own sexuality. In addition to Erika's work, almost a third of the book is dedicated to other comics artists, adding other unique voices and comics. There's also a bunch of bonus stuff too! With a few bonus comics and some behind-the-scenes stuff about OJST.
name: Volume Two

description:
The Second Revolution is about to begin. Can ONE person really save a world ruled by madmen with super humans as their slaves?

This issue - Killian has launched his assault on Los Angeles in the search for Kane. Meanwhile, Kane is trying to free another Meta-Soldier like him to help in the resistance.

"Silence is an invigorating and stimulating read; each submission provokes and engages the imagination as one glides from panel-to-panel, conjuring voices, touching on all the senses, to add to each unfolding drama. This is an experience that's certainly compounded in subsequent readings." - A Place to Hang Your Cape

40+ pages with 4 powerful silent stories about silence, from the best new talent in comics.
name: Volume Four: Silence

description:
Renaissance

The group sets out for home, joined by a new ally. They'll have to keep a low profile on their return if they hope to avoid more giant worms, or bands of the raving mutants they call Holos. Worse still, scratching at the back of Red's mind is the sinking feeling that things aren't quite right back home...
name: Renaissance

volume.name: Ant-Man: Die Offizielle Vorgeschichte Zum Film

description: When peace talks between two rival nations are threatened, the call goes out to the ultra-top-secret International Sneaky Service's number one agent: Secret Squirrel! And since the thing threatening the talks is a medieval ghost, the call also goes out to the not-so-secret Scooby gang!
name: I Spy Something...Boo! Part 1

description: After narrowly escaped the clutches of the mighty "Galoo'th", the team found themselves in the under-sand city of Zaphon. The team quickly realised that the real threats weren't above the sand they were below it, as "D'Thlu" mind controlled " amal" into attacking "Captain Aphi" in order to commandeer STARBURN!

Agnoeema

Set over three time periods, Agnoeema is a meditation on time, art and knowledge. Follow moments in the lives of a Greek sculptor, a modern scholar and a far-future... something, as their stories intertwine and resonate across the years. Agnoeema is a comic unlike any other.
name: Agnoeema

description:
Blow Your Men Down

Freedom and pirates clash as The Stranger and Obadiah Dirt are carried off to Madagasgar! Can their friends save them or is this really ... The End?
name: Blow Your Men Down

description: Reprinting Simon & Kirby's classic "I Want Your Man" and "The Savage in Me," originally published in 1950.

One night during a solitary trip to Italy, the straitlaced Regina spends the night with a dangerous gigolo! She can't believe a smart lawyer like herself would give herself to a man she just met... This was how daringly irresistible this man Nico was to women. Nico seems to be somewhat of a celebrity in his hometown. But Regina didn't know that he is actually a renowned prince!
name: Vol. 1

description: It was a fake wedding devised to make her sister happy. Only Rita should have known about her plan. Even her boss, Sakir, whose name she used for the groom shouldn't have known.... So why is he standing in the aisle, clad in a caftan fit for a king? He then spoke to the pale-faced Rita. "You must come with me to my home country as my bride. For business."
name: Vol. 1

description: Victoria is shocked when her best friend is in an accident along with her husband. Who would have thought the couple might die, leaving behind their baby? She's sure that stone-cold Connor North, billionaire businessman and the other person named as Dylan's guardian, has zero interest in children. Victoria's the only person left to raise Dylan with love. But it turns out that Connor wants to raise him! He argues that his wealth can provide the best environment for the baby, but what is he really up to? Victoria finds out before long-when he melts her heart with a kiss, both of them drenched from the rain...
name: Vol. 1

description: Ally's husband died in a car accident 4 months ago with an unknown woman in the passenger seat. The woman is soon identified as the wife of a well-known Italian duke. Not knowing what to do with her grief, Ally flies to Rome in the hope of meeting the woman's widower and consoling each other over their loss... However, not only is she turned away by the security guards at the gate of the duke's mansion, she is abducted by a man named Gino, who throws her into a prison cell! What is going on...?
name: Vol. 1

description: When the wealthy Alfred Wingate dies, his personal assistant, Cynthia, is utterly confused. He has left her his mansion in his will! Cynthia thought she was in love with Alfred's grandson Graham. But when she finds out he is cheating, she breaks off the engagement. But the terms of the will won't allow her to refuse the inheritance, and she's stuck with the mansion. On top of all this, Graham's brother, Rick, treats her with contempt, believing she tricked his wealthy grandfather!
name: Vol. 1

description: "You're not the type of girl who can attract a man. If you get proposed to within the next month, I'll give you a thousand dollars!" Charlotte is a talented graphic designer, who spends her days in baggy jeans with ruffled hair. She knew her best friend, Gabe, doesn't see her as a lady, but if he's going to make such a bet, she can't just take it lying down! Charlotte decides to get back at Gabe by dramatically transforming herself...
name: Vol. 1

description: "I love you, not as my boss but as a man." It had been 2 months since Kate spent a night of passion with her boss, Michael, whom she secretly loves. But the next day, Michael cruelly tells her that their relationship must strictly be kept to business. Kate cannot forget about that night, and tells Michael how she feels... In fact, Michael grew up in an orphanage. He had a difficult childhood and now finds it impossible to love. Can Kate's love change Michael?
name: Million Dollar Men I

description: Liv Winchester has a rough life, being both a single mother and a full-time nurse under the strict Dr. Stefano Lucarelli. Shamed and insulted by her ex-husband four years ago, she's lost all confidence in her body. When he disappeared from the scene altogether, she took on all costs of raising a child on her own. One night when her car won't start, Liv finds that Stefano might not be the man she fears, but one of the most kind and generous people she's ever met. Dashing through the snow, on a trip to Italy to meet his family, might lead her to be a sleigh-bell bride!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Short volleyball player Nao hides a few secrets under an energetic and enthusiastic exterior. He's insecure about his height and volleyball skills; not to mention his relationship with the tall volleyball team star and Nao's oldest friend, Nawa, gets more than a little confusing after Nawa kisses him! Jealousy, growing up, and more than a few pokes in the hair whorl are in order for Nao to work things out! A story about love, growth and trust. Also, men in sports wear!

Contents

  • Kiss Upon the Hair Whorl
  • Hold Me Over the Net
  • The Shape of Love
  • Green Jade Wind
  • Beam of Sunlight Upon the Hair Whorl!
name: Vol. 1

description: Supermodel Lydia took part in a fashion show organized for a charity for disadvantaged children. But the money from the show disappeared, and it was Lydia's mother who stole the money! Lydia cannot accept that this is what happened, even after being investigated by the police...because she blames herself for her mother's unhappiness. It is the wealthy Christiano who lends Lydia a helping hand in her time of need. Although his intentions are to spend the night with her!
name: Vol. 1

description: "Come with me," her husband demands. Stacia hasn't seen Rico in over a year but he hasn't changed at all. His arrogant attitude, his alluring eyes... The free-spirited art lover Stasia and the workaholic billionaire Rico fell passionately in love, but Rico's sister's cruel lie ruined everything. But when his sister is involved in a serious accident she calls for Stacia. Perhaps she is trying to make up for what she did? Stasia makes her way to Sicily, where memories of love await her.
name: Vol. 1

description: "My dream is to be happily married!" Helen, filled with the desire to fall in love, visits the Love Mansion, where a legend claims that if any unmarried woman stays at the mansion on her birthday, the next man she meets will be the man of her destiny! However hearing strange noises in the darkness, Helen starts to regret her idea. "It was reckless for me to come here on my own." Suddenly a large shadow appears in front of her! Who could this be...?
name: Vol. 1

description: In order to meet up with her sister and her husband, who live in politically unstable Zimbabwe, Emily travels on her own to Zanzibar. Her biggest mistake is to accept the charming words of a French trader who offers her a free ride in a yacht in return for her services as a crew member. This man turns out to be a drug dealer, and after being exposed by the sheikh, the trader offers Emily as a gift! The sheikh thinks she is a prostitute, and her attempts to convince him otherwise fall on deaf ears. And now, she finds herself held captive in the luxurious palace...!
name: Vol. 1

description: Verity is looking to make a fresh start in her hometown, leaving her company and former life behind in London. While on the road, a young girl suddenly jumps out in front of her car and Verity ends up taking the girl to the hospital. Verity is shocked to find out that the girl is actually the daughter of Silas, the man who once tossed her aside. The two were star-crossed lovers, and despite pledging their eternal love to each other, Verity left for New York, while Silas married another woman and pursued his dream of opening his own business. When he suddenly shows up at her door, he makes a cold demand: "Stay out of my life."
name: Vol. 1

description: This anthology of every Nuke and Pave strip ever drawn pits our heroes against monstrous media moguls, self-absorbed teenage vampires, and a tycoon who forces Pave to reveal his true identity.

MANIAC MURDERER

After the ghastly, gruesome and murderous rampage killing of a young lady by the Whitechapel Murderer in London, 1888. The Whitechapel Murderer returns to his hometown of Bray where he blends back into normal life with the other Villagers unaware of his heinous deeds. While back in his hometown he targets his next victim, a young girl. Is the Whitechapel Murderer prepared to abduct this innocent young girl so close to home and risk being exposed and caught by the police?
name: Maniac Murderer

description: Something's fishy around here... It must be a new Digital Exclusive! Archie and friends are gathering up their poles and tackle boxes and heading to the water for some nice, relaxing fishing. Although when the Riverdale gang is involved, it's probably not going to be so relaxing, is it? See if these flukes can reel in a whopper, or if they end up all wet!
name: Surprise Size; Fishy Motive

description:
Is he a God, a girl, or both?

One day, a girl (Jeena) that was on a school trip at a museum accidentally breaks an ancient mystical vase. This vase kept thirteen (13) demons inside due to a curse. Upon breaking the vase they were suddenly released. The guardian (Argox) in charge of these creatures is now brought back from another realm. And because he couldn´t stay in this world without a physical body he had to cohabit a human body in order to stay on earth, so he chooses the body of Jeena, and now they both have to share the same body until Argox returns all the demons inside the vase, or else the world will be doomed!

BLACK EYES is a silent comic about a farmer, Kane, that battled a beast possessed by an unknown entity. In defeating the beast, he became possessed by the same being. Kane then goes on to fight others who want to possess this power, and we learn how he comes to terms with his new destiny.

Everything Old...

For more than two centuries, the Blue Baron has conquered alien invaders, maniacal mutants and super-powered psychopaths but will he be able to conquer -- 8th grade?! Sitcomics proudly presents The Blue Baron #1 - a bodyswap comedy with super-powers that shows what happens when a 300 year old hero switches bodies with a 13 year old zero! Written by TV sitcom veteran Darin Henry (Seinfeld, The Ellen Show, KC Undercover) with art by industry legends Ron Frenz (Spider-Man, Spider-Girl, Thor) and Sal Buscema (Hulk, The Avengers, Captain America), The Blue Baron #1 serves to introduce comic book fans to a whole new shared universe of heroes and villains. Sitcomics believes that 21st century readers deserve to read about 21st century heroes and once you've read this 64 page self-contained epic, we think you'll understand why we say that Sitcomics is TV you read!
name: Everything Old...

description: Southwest United States, in the Mojave Desert on the border of Arizona, the President officially inaugurates a new military complex - a secret base with a warehouse full of weapons and nuclear warheads. But during the visit, a terrorist group attacks and tries to eliminate the President, and a mysterious woman suddenly appears out of the blue...
name: Shadows 1/2

description:
The shadowy order known as the Tal-Ifatiir are on a quest to destroy the demon lord, Aghal-Paraag. To this end, their leader, the Immortal Ralaan ad-Zaliir, sends them into a dangerous, unknown land to capture a powerful witch who seeks to wreak havoc upon the land.

However, Chadhiyana, the order's first female member, holds a deadly secret about the night she helped capture the witch. As the company journeys to Aghal-Paraag's prison, one misfortune after another befalls them. Is it the witch's curse working against them or something even deadlier that only Chadhiyana knows?

Rushed through basic and shipped off to the distant colonies, belligerent conscript Natalie Assenburg finds herself with a lot to prove. Not just to herself, but to her team and to her new commander, the dismissive Colonel Thessinger. First impressions count, but will Nattie and her newly-issued drone be up to the task when the rookies are thrown into a massive training exercise?

The Blue Elves of Ennlya, a small port town of Nordrenn, have been murdered!

Lanawyn, a Blue Elf, and Turin, her human ally, set out to discover who is responsible. The trail they uncover leads back to a clan of Yrlans - Northern men who hate Elves.

At the same time, Vaalann, a young Blue Elf, undergoes a dangerous test, that of the Water of the Senses. Her future, as divined by The Mother Prophetess, is closely linked to the Sacred Crystal... A powerful artifact, which enables the wielder to control the Ocean itself!

Could Vaalann be the messiah that the Blue Elves have been waiting generations for?
name: The Crystal of the Blue Elves 1/2

description:
Fallout

Following the fallout from a storm of supernatural proportions, city residents struggle to make sense of the world around around them. The Alterhuman, Star, has disappeared and as erstwhile companions, Mim and D, search for him they stumble across an unexpected body, strewn amongst rubble. Meanwhile, an escape artist performs seemingly impossible feats in the streets of the city.

Falling Star is an original ongoing comic series created, written and drawn by Crisitan Roux. Focusing on a number of super-powered characters each trying to reconcile the nature of their gift, or curse, and their place in the world confronting them. Currently, a twice yearly publication with an emphasis on producing a high quality comic both in story and art. Each issue features a full colour wrap-around cover and contains 24-28 internal pages of grayscale art.
name: Fallout

description:
1864, under an imaginary Second Empire, Napoléon III uses his army and his secret service to study certain phenomena relating to the occult and to popular legends. His goal is quite simple: achieving world supremacy.

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverManchu & Thierry Gioux1
VarVariant CoverMahmud A. Asrar (a) & Stephane Paitreau (c)2
name: Zelda 1/2

description:
The Long Year collects 12 short stories including: This Won't Last, North Port, Weightless, Speck of Dust, Bird Lungs, Sand Particles, Oculus, The Last Outpost, The Hunter's Moon, To Become Day, It's All Relative, and Paper Cranes.

The stories in the book range from short Sci-fi stories to longer stories dealing with mortality. Each story is a nugget of a thought with a touch of my off-beat story telling style.

Experience the true scale of the Marvel Cinematic Universe with the latest entry in Marvel's ART OF series. Armed with the astonishing ability to shrink in size but increase in strength, master thief Scott Lang must embrace his inner hero and help his mentor, Dr. Hank Pym, protect his spectacular Ant-Man suit from a new generation of towering threats. Stars Paul Rudd and Michael Douglas take up the mantles of Scott Lang and Hank Pym as Marvel's Ant-Man brings the founding Avengers member to the big screen for the first time. In this keepsake volume, explore script secrets and production designs that showcase the creativity of Marvel's talented filmmakers. With intricate concept art, full-color photography from the set and finished film, and commentary from the filmmakers, including Director Peyton Reed, this collectible will delight new and old fans alike!
name: HC

description: There are things that exist in the shadows that ordinary people know nothing of. Another world that lies underneath our very own; a world of demons, monsters, djinns, mummies, werewolves, vampires and demi-gods. It's in this world that Darius Mistry and his friend, Amos Golem, operate as Paranormal Investigators for hire. Whether it's being hired by ghosts to solve their own murders, breaking up rings of soul-smugglers or saving the city from an outbreak of lycanthropy -- these detectives are always on the case! The first issue of a 5-part series.

Deepak Chopra presents the tales of the immortal gods and goddesses of Indian myth who reign over humanity and wield the forces of the Universe. At first, I shed tears at the massacre of my kin at the hands of a ruthless king. The Axe mocked me. I felt the anger well up in my heart, screaming to be unleashed. The Axe encouraged me. I tried to veer myself away from the path of vengeance. The Axe whispered in my ears. Once, I was a scholar, a man at peace with his soul. But now who I am is long gone. I have vowed to rid the earth of my enemies. The man I used to be is dead, his identity washed away in a deluge of retribution. Once, there was a hermit named Rama, now there is only The Axe. This story takes a look at the metamorphosis of a peace loving hermit named Rama into one of the most feared warriors on the planet. When a tyrant massacres his family, Rama picks up the Axe and vows to rid the earth of Kings. Witness the rage and fury of a man pushed too far as he embarks on a bloody campaign, and the thirst for vengeance transforms him into the very thing he set out to fight.

Deepak Chopra presents the tales of the immortal gods and goddesses of Indian myth who reign over humanity and wield the forces of the Universe. The story of Saraswati, she of the white swan, daughter of Brahma and the wise but temperamental goddess of wisdom and learning. In an ancient age ridiculed by his wife for his lack of intellectual finesse, a young man named Kalidasa embarks on a quest to achieve enlightenment. His prayers are answered as Saraswati blesses him with the wisdom of sages and prophesizes his destiny to be the greatest of all poets, yet lost in his youthful enthusiasm the young poet hastily composes a hymn in honor of the goddess marveling at not only her wisdom and prowess, but also her ethereal beauty. Miffed at this seeming affront the goddess puts a curse on Kalidasa that he shall lose his glib tongue in the holy city of Varansi.
